==English==

===Etymology===
From the New Latin [[cephal]], from the Greek [[κεφαλο-]] (''kephalo-''), from [[κεφαλ]] (''kephal'', meaning ''head''), from the Proto-Indo-European root ''ghebh-el-''; + [[thorax]].

